The paper discusses physical-layer security in a free-space optical (FSO) link, which involves channel estimation and information-theoretic metrics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Physics (cs.PH), or Optics (cs.OH) sub-categories. Among these, cs.IT and cs.CR are the most likely sub-categories as they directly relate to the paper's focus on information-theoretic metrics and secure message transmission. cs.NI is also likely as the paper discusses a scenario of satellite-to-ground laser communications. cs.PH and cs.OH are less likely but still possible as they relate to the physical properties of the FSO channel.
